               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17780429-58-person539">
                  JOHN
                   BROUGHTON
               <interp inst="t17780429-58-person539" type="surname" value="BROUGHTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17780429-58-person539" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17780429-58-person539" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>

               <p>I am a watchman. I saw the prisoner break the bars belonging to Mr. Deverall's house; they were fixed before the kitchen window; he wrenched off three, and then took them to a gateway opposite: I secured him and took him to the watch-house. I compared the bars with the place they were taken from, and they fitted exactly.</p>

               <p>[
               <persName id="t17780429-58-person540">
                  William
                   Stiles
               <interp inst="t17780429-58-person540" type="surname" value="Stiles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17780429-58-person540" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17780429-58-person540" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             Jones, the constable, produced the bars in court.]</p>

               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>

               <p>I found the little bar I had under my coats they laid hold of me and said I stole it.</p>

               <p>
                  <rs id="t17780429-58-verdict275" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17780429-58-verdict275" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>

               <p>Tried by the Second London Jury before Mr. RECORDER.</p>
